history.content: I’m doing that plus Physics 7B, a few extracurriculars, and some breadths this semester. It’s challenging but doable. 126 has had a roughly constant high workload of homeworks and labs so far, and 162 the same with HWs and project stuff since the first project came out. They’re kind of a nice pair in the sense that they’re completely different classes. Difficulty of 162 is largely a function of your group; my group is awesome so it’s a lot of work as expected but manageable. As long as you feel reasonably comfortable with 70’s probability section (which is reviewed, but at a fast pace) and most of 61C, I think it’s a fine schedule.
